'''Hannibal Mejbri''' ({{langx|ar|حَنِّبَعْل المجبري}}; born 21 January 2003), also known mononymously as '''Hannibal''', is a professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for {{English football updater|Burnley}} club [[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]] and the [[Tunisia national football team|Tunisia national team]].

Mejbri joined the [[Manchester United F.C. Reserves and Academy|Manchester United youth system]] in 2019 from [[AS Monaco FC|Monaco]]. He had previously spent time at the [[INF Clairefontaine|Clairefontaine]] academy. He made his senior debut for the club in a Premier League game in May 2021. Mejbri spent the 2022–23 season [[loan (association football)|on loan]] to [[EFL Championship|Championship]] club [[Birmingham City F.C.|Birmingham City]]; he was a regular in the side, and scored his first senior goal. Mejbri was sent on loan to [[La Liga]] club [[Sevilla FC|Sevilla]] in 2024 before joining Championship club [[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]] later that year, which was promoted to the Premier League at the end of the 2024–25 season.

Born in France to Tunisian parents, Mejbri represented his birth country at [[France national under-16 football team|under-16]] and [[France national under-17 football team|under-17]] levels. He made his senior international debut for Tunisia in 2021.

==Early life==
Mejbri was born in [[Ivry-sur-Seine]] (suburban [[Paris]]),<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.asmonaco.com/en/joueurs/hannibal-mejbri/|title=Profile|access-date=30 June 2020|website=asmonaco.com|archive-url=http://web.archive.org/web/20190723051440/https://www.asmonaco.com/en/joueurs/hannibal-mejbri/|archive-date=2019-07-23}}</ref> and grew up in [[20th arrondissement of Paris|the city's 20th arrondissement]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Pauline |title=Hannibal Mejbri : du 20e arrondissement à la Coupe du Monde de foot – Mon Petit 20e |url=https://monpetit20e.com/hannibal-mejbri/ |access-date=2024-01-08 |language=fr}}</ref> He joined [[Paris FC]] in 2009.<ref name="fff">{{cite web|url=https://www.fff.fr/equipe-nationale/joueur/9591-mejbri-hannibal/fiche.html|title=Profile|access-date=28 May 2021|website=fff.fr|language=fr}}</ref> In 2016, it was reported that he was being scouted by several English clubs, including [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]], [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]], [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]] and [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]], and spent time on trial with the latter.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://talksport.com/football/161943/manchester-united-manchester-city-liverpool-and-arsenal-all-tracking-former-gunners/|title=Manchester United, Manchester City, Liverpool and Arsenal ALL tracking former Gunners trialist Hannibal Mejbri|date=23 November 2016|access-date=30 June 2020|website=talksport.com}}</ref> He also spent time studying at the prestigious [[INF Clairefontaine]] academy.<ref name="leparisien">{{cite web|url=https://www.leparisien.fr/sports/ile-de-france/hannibal-mejbri-j-ai-appris-a-vivre-avec-de-la-jalousie-autour-de-moi-09-06-2018-7762659.php|title=Hannibal Mejbri : "J'ai appris à vivre avec de la jalousie autour de moi"|trans-title=Hannibal Mejbri: "I learned to live with jealousy around me"|first=Laurent|last=Pruneta|date=9 June 2018|access-date=30 June 2020|website=leparisien.fr|language=fr}}</ref> His elder brother, Abderrahmen Mejbri, is a sporting coach working for the [[Vietnam national football team]] and [[Pho Hien FC]], a Vietnamese youth development club.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.leparisien.fr/sports/ile-de-france/football-l-ancien-educateur-de-l-acbb-tente-l-aventure-au-viet-nam-29-04-2019-8062656.php |title=Football : l'Ancien éducateur de l'ACBB tente l'aventure au Viêt Nam |date=29 April 2019 }}</ref>

==Club career==
===Early career===
Despite interest from English clubs, Mejbri had a short spell with [[Athletic Club de Boulogne-Billancourt|Boulogne-Billancourt]], before joining [[AS Monaco FC|Monaco]] in 2018 for a fee of €1&nbsp;million.<ref name="leparisien" /> Although initially impressed by Monaco's youth development,<ref name="leparisien" /> Mejbri became disillusioned by the Monégasque club within a year of signing, with his parents claiming that the Ligue 1 side had breached contract agreements.<ref name="MEN1">{{cite web|url=https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/transfer-news/man-united-hannibal-mejbri-wiki-16713567|title=Who is Hannibal Mejbri? Profile of Manchester United new signing|first=Charlotte|last=Duncker|date=11 August 2019|access-date=30 June 2020|website=manchestereveningnews.co.uk}}</ref>

In 2019, he was being tracked by clubs across Europe, including the German, French and Spanish champions, [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]],<ref name="MEN1" /> [[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|Paris Saint-Germain]] and [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]] respectively.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://bleacherreport.com/articles/2849237-manchester-united-confirm-signing-of-hannibal-mejbri-from-monaco|title=Manchester United Confirm Signing of Hannibal Mejbri from Monaco|first=Matt|last=Jones|date=11 August 2019|access-date=30 June 2020|website=bleacherreport.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11667/11774734/manchester-united-confident-of-signing-hannibal-mejbri-from-monaco|title=Manchester United confident of signing Hannibal Mejbri from Monaco|date=1 August 2019|access-date=30 June 2020|website=skysports.com}}</ref> Mejbri said that he was experiencing the "dark side of football" prior to signing with Manchester United and that he had not played football for nearly four months. Before signing, he was back home in Quartier des Amandiers and was training on his own with his sibling.<ref>{{Citation |title=1 vs 1 : Hannibal Mejbri " Avant de signer à Manchester, j'avais arrêté le foot pendant 4 mois " |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DkdOR3ExwKQ&t=803s |access-date=27 November 2022 }}</ref>

===Manchester United===
[[File:Manchester United v Norwich City, 16 April 2022 (02).jpg|thumb|200px|Mejbri warming up for [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] in 2022.]]

On 11 August 2019, [[Premier League]] side Manchester United announced on their website that they had reached an agreement with Monaco to sign Mejbri, with the youngster reportedly rejecting moves to other English clubs.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/man-utd-academy-deals-for-two-u23s-and-five-u18s|title=United accounce new academy deals|first=Adam|last=Marshall|date=11 August 2019|access-date=30 June 2020|website=manutd.com}}</ref> The fee paid by the Manchester club was believed to be around €5&nbsp;million, possibly rising to €10&nbsp;million in add-ons.<ref name="MEN1" /><ref name="Standard1">{{cite web|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/manchesterunited/who-is-hannibal-mejbri-man-utd-new-signing-16-from-as-monaco-a4210756.html|title=Who is Hannibal Mejbri? Man Utd's new 16-year-old signing from AS Monaco|date=11 August 2019|access-date=30 June 2020|website=standard.co.uk}}</ref>

Mejbri settled quickly into Manchester United's youth teams, progressing to the under-23 squad despite still being 17.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/manchester-united/story/4085483/forget-sideshow-bob-sneersmanchester-uniteds-mejbri-wants-last-laugh|title=Forget 'Sideshow Bob' sneers, Manchester United's Mejbri wants last laugh|first=Rob|last=Dawson|date=18 April 2020|access-date=30 June 2020|website=espn.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://thepeoplesperson.com/2020/04/07/hannibal-mejbri-why-manchester-united-fans-are-so-excited-213828/|title=Hannibal Mejbri – why Manchester United fans are so excited|date=7 April 2020|access-date=30 June 2020|website=thepeoplesperson.com}}</ref> Mejbri made his debut playing for the [[Manchester United F.C. Reserves and Academy|Manchester United U21]] side against [[Salford City F.C.|Salford City]] in the [[2020–21 EFL Trophy]] on 9 September 2020.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/salford-city-0-man-utd-6-match-report-in-the-efl-trophy|title=Manchester United Under-21s hit six at Salford |first=Michael |last=Plant|date=9 September 2020|access-date=9 September 2020|website=ManUtd.com}}</ref> He signed a new contract with United in March 2021.<ref>{{cite news |title=Hannibal commits future to Manchester United by signing new long-term contract |url=https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/hannibal-manchester-united-new-contract-20174401 |work=Manchester Evening News |date=15 March 2021|access-date=28 May 2021}}</ref> On 20 May 2021, he won the [[Manchester United F.C. Reserves and Academy#Players of the Year|Denzil Haroun Reserve Player of the Year]] award.<ref>{{cite news |title=Hannibal Mejbri named Manchester United Under-23s Player of the Year |url=https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/manchester-united-hannibal-mejbri-award-20643956 |work=Manchester Evening News |date=20 May 2021|access-date=28 May 2021}}</ref> made his senior debut three days later in a 2–1 win over [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]] in the final game of the [[2020–21 Premier League|Premier League]] season; he came on to replace [[Juan Mata]] in the 82nd minute.<ref>{{cite news|first=Gary|last=Rose |title=Wolves 1–2 Manchester United: Nuno Espirito Santo beaten in final game |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/57066741|work=BBC Sport|date=23 May 2021|access-date=23 May 2021}}</ref>

====Loan to Birmingham City====
On 29 August 2022, Mejbri joined [[EFL Championship|Championship]] club [[Birmingham City F.C.|Birmingham City]] on loan for the [[2022–23 Birmingham City F.C. season|2022–23 season]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Hannibal loan to Championship club|url=https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/man-utd-midfielder-hannibal-signs-for-birmingham-city-on-loan|website=ManUtd.com|publisher=Manchester United|date=29 August 2022|access-date=29 August 2022}}</ref>  On 10 February 2023, he scored his first senior goal, against [[West Bromwich Albion]], with a surprise free-kick.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Scott |first1=Ged |title=Birmingham City 2–0 West Bromwich Albion |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/64507487 |website=BBC Sport |access-date=11 February 2023}}</ref>

====Return to Manchester United====
On 16 September 2023, Mejbri scored his first Premier League goal for Manchester United in a 3–1 home defeat against [[Brighton & Hove Albion F.C.|Brighton]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.france24.com/en/live-news/20230916-brighton-rock-man-utd-as-old-trafford-crisis-mounts |title=Brighton rock Man Utd as Old Trafford crisis mounts |publisher=France 24 |date=16 September 2023 }}</ref>

====Loan to Sevilla====
On 15 January 2024, Manchester United sent Mejbri on loan to [[La Liga]] club [[Sevilla FC|Sevilla]] until the end of the [[2023–24 Sevilla FC season|season]], with an optional buy-clause reported to be around €20 million.<ref>{{Cite web |date=15 January 2024 |title=Hannibal leaves for Sevilla |url=https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/hannibal-leaves-man-utd-for-sevilla-on-loan-for-rest-of-season |access-date=15 January 2024 |series=Manchester United F.C. |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=15 January 2024 |title=The French-born Tunisian international midfielder arrives from Manchester United |url=https://sevillafc.es/en/actual/news/hannibal-signs-loan-2024 |access-date=17 January 2024 |website= |publisher=Sevilla F.C. |language=en|archive-url=http://web.archive.org/web/20240115202849/https://sevillafc.es/en/actual/news/hannibal-signs-loan-2024|archive-date=2024-01-15}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=16 January 2024 |title=Official: Hannibal leaves Man Utd to join Sevilla on loan |url=https://www.besoccer.com/new/official-hannibal-leaves-man-utd-to-join-sevilla-on-loan-1297760 |access-date=17 January 2024 |website=BeSoccer |language=en}}</ref>

=== Burnley ===
[[File:Queen Park Rangers v Burnley 26042025 (23).jpg|thumb|200px|Mejbri playing for [[EFL Championship]] club [[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]].]]

On 28 August 2024, Mejbri joined [[EFL Championship]] club [[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]] on a four-year contract.<ref>{{cite news |title=Mejbri is a Claret! |url=https://www.burnleyfootballclub.com/content/mejbri-is-a-claret |access-date=28 August 2024 |publisher=Burnley FC |date=28 August 2024}}</ref> On 11 April 2025, he scored his first goal for Burnley during the 42nd match of the [[2024–25 EFL Championship]] in a 2–1 win against [[Norwich City F.C.|Norwich City]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Burnley v Norwich City 2024/25 |url=https://www.efl.com/match-centre/g2450639? |access-date=11 April 2025 |publisher=EFL}}</ref>

==International career==
===France===
Mejbri made 12 appearances for France at [[France national under-16 football team|under-16]] level and three appearances at [[France national under-17 football team|under-17]] level.<ref name="fff"/>

He was first called for France at under-16 level in September 2018. He made his debut on 25 September 2018, in a 3–2 defeat to [[Denmark national under-17 football team|Denmark]]. He scored a goal on 22 April 2019, in a 4–0 win against [[Ivory Coast national under-17 football team|Ivory Coast]].{{citation needed|date=April 2023}} In the same year, he was called up for the first time to the under-17 national team.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Duncker |first=Charlotte |date=2019-08-11 |title=Who is Hannibal Mejbri? Profile of Manchester United new signing |url=https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/transfer-news/man-utd-hannibal-mejbri-wiki-16713567 |access-date=2023-04-02 |website=Manchester Evening News |language=en}}</ref> He scored two goals on his debut for the team on 22 October 2019, in an 8–0 win against [[Gibraltar national under-17 football team|Gibraltar]] in [[2020 UEFA European Under-17 Championship qualification]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=France – Gibraltar 8:0 |url=https://www.flashscore.com/match/Ol4EroJ9/#/match-summary/match-summary |access-date=2023-04-03 |website=flashscore.com |language=en}}</ref>

===Tunisia===
In May 2021, Mejbri was called up for [[Tunisia national football team|Tunisia national team]] for the first time,<ref name="MEN">{{cite web |last=Duncker |first=Charlotte |date=11 August 2019 |title=Who is Hannibal Mejbri? Profile of Manchester United new signing |url=https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/transfer-news/man-united-hannibal-mejbri-wiki-16713567 |access-date=30 June 2020 |website=manchestereveningnews.co.uk}}</ref> committing his international future to his parents' homeland.<ref>{{cite web |last=Critchley |first=Mark |date=6 February 2020 |title=Why Manchester United wonderkid Hannibal Mejbri deserves your attention |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/premier-league/manchester-united-news-hannibal-mejbri-fa-youth-cup-quarter-final-leeds-united-a9320416.html |url-access=subscription |url-status=live |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/20220509/https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/premier-league/manchester-united-news-hannibal-mejbri-fa-youth-cup-quarter-final-leeds-united-a9320416.html |archive-date=9 May 2022 |access-date=30 June 2020 |website=independent.co.uk}}</ref> He earned his first cap on 5 June during a friendly game coming on as a second-half substitute against the [[DR Congo national football team|DR Congo]] at the [[Hammadi Agrebi Stadium]] in [[Tunis]], replacing [[Youssef Msakni]] in the 46th minute; the match ended in a 1–0 victory.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Match Report of Tunisia vs Congo DR – 2021-06-05 – FIFA Friendlies – Global Sports Archive |url=https://globalsportsarchive.com/match/soccer/2021-06-05/tunisia-vs-congo-dr/2376878/ |website=globalsportsarchive.com}}</ref><ref name="Standard">{{cite web |date=11 August 2019 |title=Who is Hannibal Mejbri? Man Utd's new 16-year-old signing from AS Monaco |url=https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/manchesterunited/who-is-hannibal-mejbri-man-utd-new-signing-16-from-as-monaco-a4210756.html |access-date=30 June 2020 |website=standard.co.uk}}</ref> In November 2021, [[Mondher Kebaier]] called him up to participate in the [[2021 FIFA Arab Cup]] in Qatar. He provided his first assist against [[Mauritania national football team|Mauritania]] in the first group match and was named man of the match in the third group match after a 1–0 win against the [[United Arab Emirates national football team|United Arab Emirates]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Marshall |first=Adam |date=28 May 2021 |title=Hannibal's international future confirmed |url=https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/hannibal-named-in-tunisia-squad-for-the-first-time |accessdate=28 May 2021 |website=ManUtd.com |publisher=Manchester United}}</ref> He was again named man of the match in a 1–0 win the semi-final against [[Egypt national football team|Egypt]]. He played almost the entire 88 minutes of regular time in [[2021 FIFA Arab Cup final|the final]],<ref>{{cite web |last=Stephen |first=Killen |date=17 December 2021 |title=Hannibal Mejbri wants Arab Cup displays to kickstart Manchester United career |url=https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/hannibal-man-united-arab-cup-22497566.amp |access-date=18 December 2021 |website=manchestereveningnews.co.uk}}</ref> before being replaced by [[Mohamed Ali Ben Romdhane]].<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |last=Findlater |first=James |date=18 December 2021 |title=Manchester United starlet Hannibal Mejbri suffers Arab Cup final heartbreak |url=https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/manchester-united-hannibal-mejbri-tunisia-22507937 |access-date=18 December 2021 |website=Manchester Evening News}}</ref> He was twice named African revelation of the year at the Africa d'Or awards, in 2021 and 2022.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Africa d’Or 2021: Hannibal Mejbri élu révélation africaine de l'année |url=https://www.espacemanager.com/africa-dor-2021-hannibal-mejbri-elu-revelation-africaine-de-lannee.html |access-date=2023-04-02 |website=Espace Manager |language=fr|archive-url=http://web.archive.org/web/20230104205511/https://www.espacemanager.com/africa-dor-2021-hannibal-mejbri-elu-revelation-africaine-de-lannee.html|archive-date=2023-01-04}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Boubaker |first=Saber Ben |date=2022-07-31 |title=Prix Africa d’Or : Hannibal Mejbri élu révélation africaine 2022 |url=https://sport.tunisienumerique.com/prix-africa-dor-hannibal-mejbri-elu-revelation-africaine-2022/ |access-date=2023-04-02 |website=Sport By TN |language=fr}}</ref>
[[File:Phase_de_match_Tunisie_-_Mali.jpg|thumb|200x200px|Mejbri playing for Tunisia against Mali at the [[2021 Africa Cup of Nations]].]]
In January 2022, Kebaier called him up to participate in the [[2021 Africa Cup of Nations]] in Cameroon. He started the first match against [[Mali national football team|Mali]], which ended in a 0–1 defeat, and was substituted in the 46th minute. In the third match against [[Gambia national football team|Gambia]], he played 22 minutes, replacing [[Hamza Rafia]] in the 68th minute. The team was ultimately eliminated in the quarterfinals by [[Burkina Faso national football team|Burkina Faso]] 0–1. On 14 November 2022, he was selected by [[Jalel Kadri]] to participate in the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]] in Qatar.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Khazri, Talbi et Abdi dans la liste de la Tunisie pour la Coupe du monde |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Khazri-talbi-et-abdi-dans-la-liste-de-la-tunisie-pour-la-coupe-du-monde/1364820 |access-date=2023-04-02 |website=L'Équipe |language=fr}}</ref> On 22 November, he made his debut in a 0–0 draw, replacing Msakni in the 80th minute of Tunisia's [[2022 FIFA World Cup Group D|Group D]] match against [[Denmark national football team|Denmark]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-11-22 |title=Tunisie – Danemark : la réaction d'Hannibal Mejbri après le match solide des Aigles de Carthage ! |url=https://www.onzemondial.com/coupe-du-monde-2022/tunisie-danemark-la-reaction-d-hannibal-mejbri-apres-le-match-solide-des-aigles-de-carthage-807268 |access-date=2024-07-06 |website=Onze Mondial |language=fr}}</ref> Mejbri was not used in the next two group matches, and Tunisia was eliminated in the group round as third-placed team. Mejbri played in two matches in the [[2023 Africa Cup of Nations qualification]] against [[Libya national football team|Libya]] and winning both games 3–0 and 1–0.

On 28 December 2023, when Tunisia's squad for the [[2023 Africa Cup of Nations]] was announced, Mejbri was at the center of a controversy when he was omitted from the list.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-01-16 |title=Where is Hannibal Mejbri? Why Tunisia and Man United midfielder is not at AFCON 2023 |url=https://www.sportingnews.com/us/soccer/news/where-hannibal-mejbri-why-tunisia-man-united-not-afcon-2023/fd716fae87de9b8933777f05 |access-date=2024-07-06 |website=sportingnews.com}}</ref> Although Kadri was clear in explaining that Mejbri had expressed his desire not to play in the competition due to his difficult situation at [[Manchester United]], some were not convinced by this argument.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-12-28 |title=AFCON 2023: Man Utd star Hannibal dropped by Tunisia |url=https://afrosportnow.com/afcon-2023-man-utd-star-hannibal-dropped-by-tunisia/ |access-date=2024-07-06}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Roberts |first=Ewan |date=2023-12-28 |title=Tunisia boss explains shock decision to leave Hannibal Mejbri out of Afcon squad |url=https://metro.co.uk/2023/12/28/tunisia-boss-explains-decision-leave-hannibal-mejbri-afcon-squad-20034600/ |access-date=2024-07-06 |website=Metro}}</ref>

== Style of play ==
A composed midfielder on the ball, head of first-team development at Manchester United, [[Nicky Butt]], compared Mejbri to his former teammates [[David Beckham]] and [[Roy Keane]] for his leadership skills. Coach [[Neil Ryan]] has also praised Mejbri, stating he has high hopes for the young playmaker.<ref>{{cite web |last=Otway |first=Jack |date=30 June 2020 |title=Man Utd have the next David Beckham and Roy Keane ready to shine after Angel Gomes exit |url=https://www.express.co.uk/sport/football/1302608/Manchester-United-transfer-news-David-Beckham-Roy-Keane-Angel-Gomes-Hannibal-Mejbri |accessdate=30 June 2020 |website=express.co.uk}}</ref> Mejbri is often described as an energetic, dynamic and determined player on the pitch. He does not hesitate to participate in defensive phases and to press the opponent, endowed with significant aggressiveness.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Couderc |first=Ervan |date=2022-11-30 |title=Hannibal Mejbri, le trésor de la Tunisie |url=https://cafecremesport.com/2022/11/30/hannibal-mejbri-le-tresor-de-la-tunisie/ |access-date=2024-07-06 |website=Café Crème Sport |language=fr}}</ref>

